<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="page-eyebrow">Denison Black Alumni Association</div>
  <h1 class="page-title">Perspectives</h1>
  <p class="series-desc">An occasional series exploring the ideas, principles, and long-term strategies that shape the work of the Black Alumni Association. Since 1975, Black alumni leaders have built programs, traditions, and networks that strengthened the experience of Black students and alumni at Denison. This series examines how the BAA, and Black alumni organizations in general, can evolve — developing the infrastructure, stewardship, and systems needed to sustain their work for future generations.</p>
</section>

